      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JILLIBY BALLERINI (4) relished the absence of Keayang Zahara to land a well-deserved Group 1 win at Melton last week and gets an immediate chance to add another. Has been runner-up to her star stablemate multiple times this campaign including the TAB Trot in NZ, the Great Southern Star and Hammerhead Mile at this circuit and distance. That form stands out in this line-up so she is clearly the one to beat. JILLIBY DREAMLOVER (3) was first up for eight weeks when second to JILLIBY BALLERINI in the Sumthingaboutmaori last week and also placed behind her in both the Great Southern Star and Kilmore Cup earlier this year. It'll be tough to turn the tables but she may strip fitter and draws well. ROCKINWITHATTITUDE (8) is going well, placing behind top two selections last week and winning two of her previous three outings. Draws wide but has won two of three attempts here. THE PRIESTESS (9) jumps in grade and draws out but landed a hat trick by winning from the outside gate here on Tuesday.",
